skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:description: {"id": "3f41fc5e-b607-4aa7-a132-8ed967aa4a1f", "value": "Used for recording types of watercraft which survive as wrecks or museums in Historic England's maritime record."}
skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:title: {"id": "1a719041-afe5-485e-a049-06a921d619c1", "value": "FISH Maritime Craft Types"}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "9a2bf34c-c75a-4120-b86f-df8b035f7288", "value": "Small vessel built or adapted to lay and recover anti submarine nets in harbours and anchorages."}

{"id": "96ddfae4-e84e-4642-8473-4079c01f1238", "value": "Large warship equipped with turret mounted guns. Intended for independent action for trade protection, reconaissance and fire support for amphibious operations."}
{"id": "6e2c600a-b160-40da-9901-e057e46ab44b", "value": "Large warship with no armour and a high speed. Used for reconnaisance and raids on enemy merchant shipping."}

{"id": "6f5c9a82-67e3-45fa-bd04-351d154c1cca", "value": "A hulk or obsolete vessel filled with cement or similar material and scuttled to block an entrance to a port or anchorage, usually as a defensive measure."}
{"id": "c16bea67-1c93-4504-8333-e7a433607faa", "value": "A sailing vessel defined by a combination of such factors as hull design, locality and rig."}
{"id": "a7cef26a-f776-4c90-a685-c02502387bb0", "value": "Oared fighting ship with ancillary sails."}
{"id": "edd9c4d8-3574-4f21-b2d5-93548a21d55b", "value": "A buoy with a compartment into which shipwrecked mariners could climb to await rescue."}
{"id": "e44e646a-6d1b-497f-8e74-af2be56f857c", "value": "A vessel used for transporting passengers or goods."}
{"id": "57e53396-2970-4df0-8230-09cacaee52c0", "value": "A relatively small and heavily built vessel equipped with large engines. Used for towing ships at sea or manouevring them in tight spaces."}
{"id": "649793d0-121a-4ca0-83b3-2f1abb5af926", "value": "A craft which is equipped for and performs hydrographic surveys."}
{"id": "74ffef64-c611-4d3b-9ab2-4c01ed8fc531", "value": "Any vessel operated by Trinity house masters and brethren in the maintenance of lighthouses, lightships, buoys and other navigation aids."}
{"id": "cd48d07e-d855-43ed-91f7-fd9de095a2a0", "value": "A vessel or craft used for catching or harvesting marine life by a variety of methods, use specific method where known."}

{"id": "8b858691-292a-4c17-9e4f-c41050ba703c", "value": "A freelance boat used off the south and east coasts of England to provide passing ships with pilots, supplies, new anchors and other gear. Some helped sailing ships and barges get underway. Generally lug-rigged. Also used for fishing. Half decked."}
{"id": "bd08e3fd-d661-444e-a142-a73043e68250", "value": "A private fighting ship under a letter of marque or financed by subscribers, shareholders or individuals."}
{"id": "257293fc-1b59-4592-b9b1-4db951bf95d9", "value": "A vessel, purpose-built or requisitioned, used for patrolling inland or coastal waters, e.g. Coastguard and Customs vessels."}
{"id": "061024eb-d826-4ec4-b1ae-ed5d8fcf935b", "value": "The class term, use more specific terms."}
{"id": "98994aad-7d2a-494d-bd6b-9bcde2c9e266", "value": "A craft built with the intention of demonstrating or advertising a novel design feature."}
{"id": "7b7b9d68-32d4-43b0-a4e8-b2b47761bda6", "value": "An old ship converted for a variety of uses for which it is not required to move under its own power."}
{"id": "a507c64d-cbee-49de-811c-95733b421585", "value": "A large ship's boat powered by oars and or an engine."}
{"id": "634bc713-148a-42cf-952f-7b3963e74632", "value": "A ship used for laying cables (often telephone cables) along the sea bed."}
{"id": "bfe7e4d5-4d83-424f-9e4d-b257bda0a7c6", "value": "Vehicle either adapted, or purpose-built, to operate on both land and sea, for example a tank or DUKW."}
{"id": "c1ebffa8-8457-490f-9907-1e7c4e266341", "value": "A vessel fitted with a catapult for launching an aircraft."}
{"id": "1e4ac170-af97-4b8e-9265-9911f90bb5b2", "value": "A flat floating framework of planks or other materials used for supporting or carrying persons or goods."}
{"id": "ef2d2d47-ab8b-4bd3-9ac8-09731209686e", "value": "All vessels, use more specific type where known."}
{"id": "555914b2-1200-4807-9b6d-2dc6aef57ed8", "value": "Vessels of various types used specifically for providing an initial training in seamanship."}
{"id": "b4cffe8e-8044-4de4-bc2b-e36648577001", "value": "A steam vessel propelled by a pair of paddle wheels amidships or a single wheel astern, driven by a reciprocating engine."}
{"id": "a47202e0-da24-44c1-b940-3358cae3e51f", "value": "A craft used to deepen shipping channels, harbours and other water courses."}
{"id": "66255b56-768b-45da-b71b-8922ec31f4ee", "value": "Generic name for a small steam or power boat often carried on board a larger vessel."}

{"id": "806a1d2e-eb62-4354-b143-cdd5a32d89ad", "value": "A barge with a lugsail rig commonly found on the River Thames in the late 19th century. Also a general term applied to the family of Deal luggers."}
{"id": "cd3470a1-2f20-41f7-b153-1fdd75eb8a73", "value": "A steam vessel propelled by rotating propellers called screws."}

{"id": "f39d4404-fc7f-4167-b6c9-9b4e228817ce", "value": "Cargo vessel or warship captured by a warship or privateer of a hostile nation in time of war, usually taken into that nation\u00ef\u00bf\u00bds mercantile, privateering or naval service."}

{"id": "f7c8390c-380c-4190-a9ae-b4b638bce9cd", "value": "Generic name for a vessel used for work rather than for recreation, transportation, or military purposes. The vessels include tugs, barges, landing craft, dredgers and standby safety vessels. Use only were the exact type of vessel is unknown."}

{"id": "d2052f63-fbc3-4041-9dff-1882e4491527", "value": "A vessel used to carry essential supplies, such as food and armaments, to naval ships in order to keep them replenished whilst on patrol. Use more specific term."}
{"id": "0e3d4332-69f9-4c78-a5a0-3f3a53b8287a", "value": "A vessel used to maintain supply or assist larger vessels. Use more specific term."}
{"id": "d5c771d5-a637-4404-816b-aad76f108c39", "value": "A vessel equipped with sealed tanks for transporting sewage and dumping it in deep water."}
{"id": "623ee394-6154-4a25-a936-825cb431ea2b", "value": "A ship that is built and primarily intended for war."}
{"id": "cbdbc569-9ae3-42d4-b966-44901b6affc9", "value": "A flat bottomed boat or hollow float of which a number are used to support a temporary bridge over a river."}
{"id": "ddfcfb34-6b79-47b0-8f5a-c080cce9bac2", "value": "A vessel with equipment for processing dead marine life whilst still at sea."}
{"id": "d2f38922-359d-40aa-8a37-ebcd06ae5911", "value": "Vessel fitted with broadcasting equipment and used for off-shore radio programme transmission."}
{"id": "73e62b2c-6d59-42d9-b2c6-9644e522fd65", "value": "Craft intended for recreation and not intended for any commercial use."}
{"id": "05756a10-909e-4716-9816-080fb3bea1c5", "value": "The largest boat belonging to a sailing vessel, and usually the means of escape from a sinking ship; powered by oars."}
{"id": "eb67e146-92e3-4b33-a399-55b9cb5f4c37", "value": "The characteristics of a sailing vessel where her type is determined by her masts and sails."}

{"id": "cb4787a2-f408-485d-942e-767b4bcb08f8", "value": "Any boat used to transfer crew from shore to an offlying vessel. May also carry the catch from a fishing boat to shore. Used as special boats by the Royal National Lifeboat Institution for conveying crew from the beach to a moored lifeboat."}
{"id": "3d7f85ea-7f85-4627-999e-6424689cd5a0", "value": "A boat used as private or domestic living accomodation."}

{"id": "c71ece56-cea0-43c4-b9d8-bec5e460a1cb", "value": "An artificial harbour, constructed using prefabricated, concrete caissons, floating breakwaters and blockships, which were towed across the channel and assembled off the coast of Normandy to assist the allied forces after the D-Day landings in June 1944."}

{"id": "3d919eea-961b-41a4-9e8c-60ca0e31c42f", "value": "Small, light, fast, all-purpose craft designed primarily for inland use. Generally flat-bottomed, often with rocker; sharp bow, sharp or transom stern, lapstrake or carvel planking. Propelled by oars, sails or motor. Used for fishing and leisure."}

{"id": "84cf83fe-92d1-44d2-a6a8-e78483c8535b", "value": "Any vessel in the service of one of the historical or modern agencies concerned with the prevention of inbound or outbound smuggling: namely the Preventive Service, the Coastguard, or the Customs and Excise. Use more specific term."}
{"id": "abcac52a-63a3-40d0-9ac4-352a119b5d1f", "value": "Small coastal vessel."}
{"id": "83b42634-458e-4b38-bfd2-921e6b6c0c80", "value": "A craft with two masts.It is usually cutter rigged on the foremast and has a small mizzen mast."}
{"id": "ba611e10-1036-47a2-b010-91b76f6d5b8e", "value": "A ship of the line mounting 100 guns or more on three gundecks."}
{"id": "3518c2ac-3205-4a77-a312-e294f550187e", "value": "A small vessel used as transport for customs officers."}

{"id": "24ffbf00-8ef5-4ef8-8b7f-8a8d81f973d5", "value": "From 1822, any vessel in the service of HM Coastguard, principally deployed on Customs and Revenue duties, i.e. anti-smuggling operations. Superseded the Preventive Service Vessel."}
{"id": "3252e578-666f-4a58-b8cd-883ad783869e", "value": "Prior to 1822 a vessel used by the customs department involved with the prevention of smuggling."}
{"id": "9498b69c-ba2b-40fe-b7e5-7a10a87488a2", "value": "A vessel with two masts, rigged as a ketch, used for coastal trading."}

{"id": "87397cbe-1d14-4725-acb1-078598230d45", "value": "A short wide-beamed Dutch craft, often used as a fishing vessel or, in the 17th and 18th centuries, a privateer due to its manoeuvrability. Fitted with a ketch rig or variations thereof. Used extensively in the North Sea."}
{"id": "b1483ae8-d2ae-4290-91bc-69f8d979c671", "value": "A small cargo boat found on the River Severn in England, with a mast which could be taken down to allow the boat to pass under low bridges."}

{"id": "fae694bb-c254-4844-a16d-fdb89b42e17d", "value": "A German coastal minelaying submarine in use during the First World War. The U Boat carried 12 mines but was otherwise unarmed with no deck gun or torpedo tubes."}
{"id": "b56354d9-fe65-4895-9b57-5501ed170dea", "value": "A craft employed to harpoon whales and bring them in to be processed."}
{"id": "d5591227-d72c-4775-8d08-a2017c62eb45", "value": "Any vessel involved in the catching or transportation of whales."}
{"id": "b3f88ad2-4008-4e59-be85-131667441076", "value": "A small warship engaged in patrolling coastal waters."}
{"id": "a23b7309-3289-45c4-bc67-2222d595492d", "value": "Two masted ship with fore and aft sails and two or more masts."}
{"id": "4a1d7f46-30c7-4fa4-89f5-25bbd588c288", "value": "A sailing vessel, generally with three masts, square rigged on the fore and main mast."}
{"id": "d2c3700a-1938-4bf9-af01-8ee197236946", "value": "A vessel with a type of rigging where the main driving sails are fixed to yards which lie square to the mast."}
{"id": "2e1a061e-646f-46b6-87ea-34ef869a1144", "value": "Two masted merchant vessel, rigged as a brig."}
{"id": "05dcad39-ac69-4d09-aef9-8dc3ab78cf0b", "value": "Two masted vessel with a square rig on both masts."}
{"id": "121561f1-4bb6-4d13-96ad-43e838b60cca", "value": "Small square rigged ship with a narrow overhanging stern."}
{"id": "326a7afb-9fd9-4cda-abd6-4caecc98616d", "value": "A small two masted craft, with oars as well as sails."}
{"id": "0c7835cc-fc59-42c0-ad1c-8a178fc28e53", "value": "A vessel for policing fishing grounds and fishing vessels."}
{"id": "8883e974-7542-4d2e-a7a3-652cc0985a1a", "value": "A dredger which can act as its own hopper and can thus transport the mud which it picks up to dump it at the desired place."}

{"id": "9fd5095b-38cc-4b35-b131-a9e9002656f8", "value": "A multihulled craft consisting of two hulls, or vakas, which are usually joined together by a frame or other structure, formed of akas. Catamarans can be sail or engine powered."}
{"id": "45c887e7-4b96-4a50-9ec3-9a5d958b0232", "value": "A vessel used for the underwater recovery of a ship and/or her contents or to assist vessels that are sinking."}
{"id": "1cb3c6c4-05ec-4914-af80-d0f5ffe54904", "value": "A small and powerful vessel used to assist vessels that are sinking or disabled at sea."}

{"id": "053f6d19-12c1-4336-a610-e5cedddea675", "value": "Satellite craft belonging to a larger vessel, usually a rowing vessel; used to pick up or set down passengers or crew when lying offshore, or stowed on board as the 'long boat' or 'jolly boat' for lifesaving purposes."}

{"id": "ad41519b-9434-405e-8bcd-eca98c8ebcaf", "value": "A type of small boat that was often carried, or towed by a larger vessel and used as a ship's boat. Dinghies can also be used recreationally as independent sailing vessels."}
{"id": "50263696-0d1c-4240-ae6a-d40391ef412e", "value": "17th/18th century lightly armed privateer, usually either a 'Dunkirker' or Dutch."}
{"id": "801518b3-c660-49d7-ba49-a697a60cce0e", "value": "A large cargo vessel, either purpose-fitted or converted, for the transportation of slaves."}
{"id": "1280afa9-7ee5-484d-bb62-1ca4a44860c4", "value": "A ship belonging to a shipping company which carries passengers on a scheduled route usually applied to steam ships only."}
{"id": "bff8f8b2-ccc4-474e-9aaa-3734d06d9645", "value": "A passenger vessel equipped to carry a large number of emigrants usually with large third class decks and plenty of cargo space."}
{"id": "325235dc-b821-4320-a74b-8ba18c1a144a", "value": "A vessel used for the transport of troops, either during wartime or for garrison duties in peacetime."}
{"id": "f25faa29-775b-4e60-bc8e-c495203ff173", "value": "Open decked vessel used for sight seeing or pleasure voyages."}
{"id": "8730678a-5278-48b5-875d-46784a41b38e", "value": "A vessel designed principally for the carriage of fare paying passengers."}

{"id": "751a7e25-3e27-4c2d-aa02-608eb0bd382f", "value": "A vessel designed for the transport of persons and goods from one place to another an a regular schedule of sailings. Use specific type were known."}
{"id": "97cd73cc-f9f8-40ec-8001-3fd058284de5", "value": "A craft available for public hire for short journeys."}
{"id": "5edf0425-9e02-4e2e-84cc-1c4035af7578", "value": "A passenger vessel equipped with recreational facilities for long voyages for pleasure and sight seeing."}
{"id": "49988bf0-4ffa-46b2-b3e4-e36c8e5f0224", "value": "A ship used for treating patients or moving them between a battle zone and a safe area."}
{"id": "cec81bb3-f38d-4945-856b-f57be22c3422", "value": "Fishing smack specialised both for working shoal water and for trawling for shrimp, predominantly in and around Morecambe Bay."}
{"id": "24f77ca6-1a0c-42c4-a0f8-034f0a77f1c1", "value": "A small warship mounting between 20 and 28 nine-pounder guns on a single deck."}
{"id": "6f9a061c-2807-4c52-af87-852d521c2ec4", "value": "A sailing ship with a sufficient numerically large gun armament to stand in the line of battle."}
{"id": "bc53a3db-546e-42b8-8206-406f25f67795", "value": "A ship of the line mounting between 90 and 98 guns on three gun decks"}
{"id": "f8e80daf-5d51-4617-8120-8cc604b2bde6", "value": "A ship of the line mounting between 64 and 80 guns typically built with two gun decks."}
{"id": "9ccebdf5-3737-423d-8e9e-f27b3cb60223", "value": "A ship of the line mounting between 46 and 64 guns"}
{"id": "667a2e72-7805-4e00-8c60-c048606a830d", "value": "A sailing frigate mounting 32 to 44 guns with the main battery on a single deck."}
{"id": "d63b2a7b-8711-4d33-bbeb-33c51bdf54c7", "value": "Small submarine with a two or three man crew. Used for special missions such as sinking warships in heavily defended harbours."}

{"id": "b33c0d1b-917b-4cc4-a6c5-e4266922d52a", "value": "Small, heavily built coble, usually fitted with lugsail and oars, used on the north-east coast of England to assist, tow, pilot, provision or otherwise attend ships."}

{"id": "bc39e422-c151-4b74-a930-5bc60cc5bde8", "value": "A small clinker-built craft, dating primarily from the 19th and early 20th centuries, fitted with oars and often a sail, usually found on the north-east coast of England and used for fishing or pilotage."}
{"id": "c41c5ac8-eec4-416e-94af-2eac7d789d1a", "value": "A small craft of wickerwork covered with waterproof material."}

{"id": "47caf75a-8789-44f2-9a3e-8f0178f0fbb1", "value": "A prefabricated cargo vessel produced in large numbers by North American shipyards during World War II to replace shipping losses caused by German submarines and replacing the earlier 'LIBERTY' ships."}
{"id": "619bd5e9-96aa-4e5d-aebd-c6ffbfed4938", "value": "A single decked cargo vessel carrying the majority of its cargo on deck."}
{"id": "8d6e2828-fd48-463c-a29a-da7c31ab099a", "value": "Cargo vessel specially constructed to carry bulk items such as grain. Does not include liquid cargoes."}

{"id": "b438a557-8266-4b2f-99bf-d4fc68e8ca48", "value": "Originally denoting a Byzantine vessel, powered by oars, from the 6th century onwards, this developed into a large Mediterranean ship with oars and a single mast, used for trade or for war transport, (e.g. during the Crusades) until the 15th century."}
{"id": "97a2c8ae-129e-4472-8af7-201f3bc29a14", "value": "A craft designed for use on canals and inland waterways. Usually 70ft long x 7ft wide though can be longer and broader."}
{"id": "32192a70-7190-43df-9273-510f46f24b37", "value": "A designed for the carriage of livestock usually cattle or sheep."}

{"id": "d63face5-2ee6-4c00-99f6-62f3854cc591", "value": "Any one of the cargo vessels of that name belonging to the different Baltic nations, in use from the mid 18th to the early 20th century. Usually ketch-rigged. Not to be confused with the oared GALEASS."}
{"id": "b832c297-c4ea-4d6b-8d1c-e5bbaac9f7e7", "value": "A cargo vessel constructed in the U.S.A. during World War II from prefabricated sections by welding."}
{"id": "da60cee2-0e6c-4905-8de5-8019e8ae182a", "value": "A cargo vessel designed to carry goods packed in large containers that can be loaded directly onto trains or lorries."}
{"id": "226019b5-26a5-4ff6-9f2e-ef0991860620", "value": "Small cargo vessel used for short coastal voyages carrying a variety of cargoes."}
{"id": "4db01827-b81f-4709-a94f-f519b936dc4f", "value": "A vessel for carrying a cargo of coal in bulk."}
{"id": "b88cf225-268f-49e0-aeaf-05d8df0ac2b2", "value": "Large cargo vessel specially built and equipped for handling large quantities of ore."}

{"id": "6d7a9601-93a8-4752-bd1d-c426c02df3e8", "value": "17th century Dutch vessel built for naval or East India service, with a relatively flat bottom and narrow hull; sometimes rendered into English as `fly-boat'."}
{"id": "0b717016-295e-4ae9-908a-ddf9e760cdd7", "value": "Shallow draft cargo vessel, often broad beamed and flat bottomed, powered by engine and or sail."}
{"id": "4d42c8ac-42a0-4b65-9ccf-5054da4ab6a5", "value": "A small cargo vessel used on the West coast of Scotland."}
{"id": "1ee7cd48-3ae5-4ea5-a42b-c08b703bf524", "value": "A vessel used for carrying cargoes, fitted with defensive weapons. Use with specific type and form where known."}
{"id": "eadf77f8-c19f-49ad-9ec8-12c6ca65921b", "value": "A ship designed specifically for the carriage of liquid cargoes, particularly oil."}
{"id": "f53f3029-2966-4a30-8255-25d4aeba228f", "value": "A craft used for the transportation of cargoes. Use specific type where known."}
{"id": "da092ed2-6ece-48af-8ddf-a730f6dbd062", "value": "A large Mediterranean cargo or transport vessel of the 15th to 17th century, usually less than 400 tons."}
{"id": "b60aab56-57d6-4b76-884a-3061f06f8958", "value": "A tug equipped with water tanks and pumps for fighting fires at sea or on the shore line."}
{"id": "0c7eddbb-6e4a-4e64-8381-2f0f07f9e216", "value": "A vessel equipped with water tanks and pumps for fighting fires at sea or on the shore line."}
{"id": "92530210-a3aa-41e6-b44e-4e96eb5f20cb", "value": "A small, single-masted merchant vessel, designed for maximum hold capacity and not for sailing ability."}
{"id": "7a5c58df-0e6d-4c81-b488-5320da09d0a4", "value": "A vessel for maintaining the buoys, hawsers and netting of a boom defence."}
{"id": "cfdd45ba-3588-499a-9ec1-949d27bdbc49", "value": "British 'M' class submarine modified to carry and launch a small sea plane."}
{"id": "2d40b0ba-c894-49ac-ae56-0e1e09cfeb90", "value": "A German coastal attack submarine in use during the First World War."}
{"id": "6b49e502-7e9a-477f-b7ae-995be791dcd0", "value": "Specially designed/fitted carriers of crew and/or supplies to offshore oil platforms."}
{"id": "b45533eb-b4ff-475a-80f6-8c6e43e4b070", "value": "A small sailing vessel armed with guns."}
{"id": "038ed83b-2990-481f-9a1f-20e16b1228f1", "value": "A small warship with a shallow draught. Used for patrol duties and shore bombardment on major rivers."}
{"id": "bad96c25-034f-463e-8bc6-d4725172f72a", "value": "Late nineteenth and early twentieth century warship armed with guns and torpedoes."}
{"id": "d868f546-d39a-45c1-a385-d8ff3e16d51a", "value": "A small warship built to operate close to the shore or in river estuaries. Used for shore bombardment and patrol duties."}

{"id": "a4bedfa4-7420-47e6-9bad-838f5b1b4da6", "value": "A small fast warship powered by diesel or petrol engines. Built during World War II for coastal patrol work and anti shipping missions close in shore"}

{"id": "716434a3-d662-42ed-a36b-e5c2de5e823a", "value": "A sailing warship armed with one or more heavy howitzers or mortars and used for bombarding shore positions. The modern equivalent is the MONITOR."}

{"id": "71ed3b55-3b03-4862-8f0a-dbd63c0c8623", "value": "Steam-powered torpedo boat developed in the early 20th century, and used in the First World War, a development of the torpedo boat destroyer, and distinct from the motor torpedo boat of WWII."}
{"id": "957d0891-bf30-4f43-b257-df8e8d5b1ee5", "value": "Shallow draft vessel used to carry ammunition."}
{"id": "fa65ad63-b1e6-4675-96b8-ae1420de4966", "value": "A vessel used as a platform for flying a barrage balloon from."}
{"id": "3879204f-852f-4bb7-ae1f-7d2480faa02b", "value": "French coasting vessel"}
{"id": "89f6dd59-6253-41e9-a3fa-6c0e552c2825", "value": "A capital warship lightly armoured but with the same gun armament and stem turbine propulsion as a DREADNOUGHT BATTLESHIP."}
{"id": "23eb2666-37b3-496b-af46-8a90ae901a03", "value": "Sailing vessel generally with three masts square rigged on the foremast only."}
{"id": "76c1bb2d-a0cd-42fe-8474-e8cfdc9f622f", "value": "Auxiliary or support vessel used for the repair of naval craft."}
{"id": "791d06ef-f85e-4a15-9693-1cfc45fc6e89", "value": "Large inshore craft with a retractable loading ramp in the bow. Used to carry tanks ashore for a beach landing or as a tank ferry."}

{"id": "4a427703-ef7c-42b5-9bd2-95e2411fc256", "value": "A ship used to process whales into saleable products."}

{"id": "e3b27a31-2c49-4548-b76f-75ca196ceb52", "value": "A fishing vessel specially designed to operate and trawl for the catching of bottom lying fish. Use with power where known."}
{"id": "9e8d6052-6e47-4213-8cf1-1a2adee96ee3", "value": "A capital warship, often steam driven, heavily armoured with armament of large calibre guns deployed in turrets."}
{"id": "83c52011-25f0-4c58-acd2-338aaf80acee", "value": "A small galley or Dutch trading vessel similar to a barge in construction."}
